OL,3,GHighlands & Eilean Siar
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FA cloudy start with outbreaks
OL,6,Fof rain. It will turn more showery
OL,7,Fduring the day with some brighter
OL,8,Fspells. The showers could be heavy,
OL,9,Fperhaps the odd rumble of thunder.
OL,10,
OL,11,CTonight:FPartly cloudy with showers or
OL,12,Frain dying out through this evening.
OL,13,FBest of the late sunshine will be in
OL,14,Fthe south, while the north coast will
OL,15,Fremain rather cloudy.
OL,16,
OL,17,CMonday:FA mainly dry, bright morning
OL,18,Fwith some sunshine. Cloud will tend to
OL,19,Fbubble up through the day to give a
OL,20,Ffew afternoon showers between sunnier
OL,21,Fintervals.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
